biography.text:
Grammy nominated and award-winning DJ Ferry Corsten has consistently appeared on the Top100DJs poll since1999, making him the longest-standing Dutch artist to have topped these rankings in 2024.
His status as a top headliner has been cemented by numerous major events and festivals across the world,including Electric Daisy Carnival, Creamfields, UNTOLD,Beyond Wonderland, Ultra Music Festival, and Tomorrowland, to name just a few.
Ferry's current sound is a seamless fusion of trance, melodic house and techno, demonstrating his unwavering commitment to the pursuit of sonic innovation. This commitment is evident in the various albums he has released throughout his career. He has earned numerous platinum and gold records for hit singles such as "Punk" and "Out of the Blue" (under the alias System F), and has collaborated and/or remixed songs by artists such as U2, Justin Bieber,Nelly Furtado, The Killers, Moby, Cascade, Duran Duran, Snow Patrol, Armin van Buuren, Tiesto, Above & Beyond, and many more.
Ferry's music is widely respected in every genre, from techno to house to trance and in 2022, he was recognized for his outstanding contributions to music by being knighted as an Officer in the Order of Oranje-Nassau by the Dutch King and Mayor of his hometown. With his motto "The Musical Journey is the Destination," Ferry Corsten's visionary attitude, approach, and contributions to the music industry have kept him at the top of his game and will continue to do so in the future.
